This file provides a collection of reusable React components designed for creating modern and animated sign-in forms and related UI elements.

## Key Components

- **`Input`**: An animated input field with a radial gradient hover effect.
- **`Label`**: A styled label component.
- **`BoxReveal`**: An animated component that reveals its children with a sliding box effect.
- **`Ripple`**: A component that displays a series of expanding ripple circles for a background effect.
- **`OrbitingCircles`**: A component that animates children in a circular orbit. It can optionally draw a path (a circle) for visualization.
- **`TechOrbitDisplay`**: A component that displays a logo or text and animates a configurable array of `OrbitingCircles` around it.
- **`AnimatedForm`**: A comprehensive component for building animated sign-in and sign-up forms. It includes features like form validation, Google login integration, and customizable fields.
- **`BottomGradient`**: A utility component for creating a subtle gradient effect, often used with buttons.

## `AnimatedForm` Props

```typescript
type FieldType = "text" | "email" | "password";

type Field = {
  label: string;
  required?: boolean;
  type: FieldType;
  placeholder?: string;
  onChange: (event: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => void;
};

type AnimatedFormProps = {
  header: string;
  subHeader?: string;
  fields: Field[];
  submitButton: string;
  textVariantButton?: string;
  errorField?: string;
  fieldPerRow?: number;
  onSubmit: (event: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => void;
  googleLogin?: string;
  onGoogleLogin?: () => void;
  goTo?: (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => void;
};
```

## Usage Example

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { AnimatedForm, Input, BoxReveal } from '@/components/ui/modern-animated-sign-in';

const SignInPage = () => {
  const [email, setEmail] = useState('');
  const [password, setPassword] = useState('');

  const handleLogin = (event: React.FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => {
    event.preventDefault();
    console.log('Login attempt:', { email, password });
    // Handle login logic here
  };

  const fields = [
    {
      label: 'Email',
      type: 'email',
      placeholder: 'example@domain.com',
      required: true,
      onChange: (e) => setEmail(e.target.value),
    },
    {
      label: 'Password',
      type: 'password',
      placeholder: '••••••••',
      required: true,
      onChange: (e) => setPassword(e.target.value),
    },
  ];

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-black">
      <AnimatedForm
        header="Welcome Back!"
        subHeader="Sign in to continue your journey with DocMed."
        fields={fields}
        submitButton="Sign In"
        googleLogin="Sign in with Google"
        onGoogleLogin={() => console.log('Google login clicked')}
        textVariantButton="Don't have an account? Sign Up"
        goTo={() => console.log('Go to sign up')}
        onSubmit={handleLogin}
        fieldPerRow={1}
      />
    </div>
  );
};

export default SignInPage;
```
